CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 20, 1962, pg. 7, reads: "NAACP YOUNG ADULT OFFICERS - Recently installed officers of the Young Adult Chapter of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People are shown examining the calendar of events for 1962. Left to right: Vann Johnson, second vice president; Miss Brenda Leach, recording secretary; Walter Wray, first vice president; Miss Rose Marie Mitchell, corresponding secretary; Hubert Ivey, president, and Miss Patricia Adams, treasurer. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Officers of Young Adult Chapter of NAACP, first row from left: Rose Marie Mitchell (Payne), Patricia Adams, and Brenda Leach; back row: Hubert Ivey, Walter Wray, and Vann Johnson, posed in Loendi Club
